Tarrant was also deeply immersed in the coarser rhetoric of the anonymous message boards 4chan and 8chan, and other online havens of white-supremacist sentiment.
The image he used to accompany his post was a long-circulating 4chan meme depicting an overly online Australian.
And his war cry, before opening fire on worshipers, was a reference to a mega-popular YouTuber who goes by PewDiePie.
In Tarrant’s world, two codes—of racist memes and romantic racist ideology, of viral YouTube videos and high-minded nativist myth—intermingle until they are indistinguishable.
In 2017, HuffPost journalist Ashley Feinberg published the style handbook of the Daily Stormer, an infamous and prominent neo-Nazi website.